                Induction stoves are prized for their energy efficiency and fast
                cooking times, operating through electromagnetic energy to heat
                pots and pans directly. Despite their advanced technology,
                induction stoves have unique repair needs. Common issues include
                malfunctioning induction coils, which can prevent the stove from
                heating properly. The touch controls or digital displays can
                also fail, making it difficult to operate the stove. Because
                induction stoves rely on complex electronics, diagnosing and
                repairing these issues often requires specialized knowledge and
                equipment. It’s crucial to hire a technician who is experienced
                with induction technology to ensure accurate and safe repairs.
                Regularly checking the cookware compatibility and keeping the
                stovetop clean can help maintain the stove’s performance.
              </p>
            </div>

