                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>Clean the Lint Trap:</b>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          Why: A clogged lint trap restricts airflow, reducing
                          the dryer's efficiency.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          How: Remove the lint screen and clean it before every
                          load.
                        </li>
                      </ul>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <b>Inspect the Vent System:</b>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          Why: A blocked vent system can cause poor airflow,
                          making the dryer take longer to dry clothes.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          How: Disconnect the vent hose and check for lint
                          buildup. Clean it out thoroughly. Consider hiring a
                          professional for a comprehensive duct cleaning if
                          needed.
                        </li>
                      </ul>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <b>Examine the Exhaust Vent:</b>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          Why: The external vent where the dryer exhausts air
                          can also be blocked.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          How: Go outside and check the vent flap to ensure it
                          opens freely and is not obstructed.
                        </li>
                      </ul>
                    </li>
                  </ul>

